HCV-GPT
Overview
HCV-GPT is an advanced AI assistant specifically designed to provide expert-level guidance on Hepatitis C virus (HCV) diagnosis and management. This tool leverages the power of OpenAI's GPT-4 Turbo model combined with retrieval augmented generation to offer insights based on the latest gold-standard recommendations from the 2020 Guidelines published by the European Association for the Study of the Liver.
Features

Interactive chat interface with real-time streaming response generation
Evidence-based responses anchored to the latest EASL HCV guidelines
User-friendly Streamlit web application with modern UI
Efficient vector similarity search using FAISS
Pre-computed embeddings for optimal performance
Diagnostic and treatment assistance for healthcare professionals

Repository Structure
Our GitHub repository (https://github.com/liveraidlab/hcv-gpt) contains:

[APP] Retrieval Augmented Generation: Contains the Streamlit application (app.py), prompt instructions (file1.docx), and vector database (vector_data folder) for the RAG implementation
Instruction Fine-Tuning Datasets: Contains all datasets used for supervised fine-tuning of the models, including training and validation sets derived from HCV guidelines
